{"id":"267214767_Note_on_quantitatively_correct_simulations_of_the_kinetic_beam-plasma_instability","abstract":"A large number of model particles is shown necessary for quantitatively\ncorrect simulations of the kinetic beam-plasma instability with the\nclouds-in-cells method. The required number of particles scales inversely with\nthe expected growth rate, as in the kinetic regime only a narrow interval of\nbeam velocities is resonant with the wave.","authors":["K. V. Lotov","I. V. Timofeev","EA Mesyats","AV Snytnikov"],"meta":["October 2014Physics of Plasmas 22(2)","DOI:10.1063/1.4907223","SourcearXiv"],"references":["261048527_Two-stream_instability_analysis_for_propagating_charged_particle_beams_with_a_velocity_tilt","260701376_Temporal_structure_of_double_plasma_frequency_emission_of_thin_beam-heated_plasma","258574382_Modeling_of_laser_wakefield_acceleration_in_the_Lorentz_boosted_frame_using_OSIRIS_and_UPIC_framework","251572199_Status_and_Prospects_of_GOL-3_Multiple_Mirror_Trap","236935970_The_effect_of_initial_conditions_on_the_electromagnetic_radiation_generation_in_type_III_solar_radio_bursts","234963286_Computationally_efficient_description_of_relativistic_electron_beam_transport_in_collisionless_plasma","234937016_Simulation_and_theory_for_two-dimensional_beam-plasma_instability","234912745_Multidimensional_electron_beam-plasma_instabilities_in_the_relativistic_regime","230908438_Multiple_Harmonic_Plasma_Emission","224983560_Generation_of_powerful_terahertz_emission_in_a_beam-driven_strong_plasmaturbulence","269001596_Numerical_particle-in-cell_methods","258797109_Generation_of_High-Power_Sub-THz_Waves_in_Magnetized_Turbulent_Electron_Beam_Plasmas","252275271_Evolution_of_a_relativistic_electron_beam-plasma_return_current_system","237053968_The_Fluid-Kinetic_Particle-in-Cell_Solver_for_Plasma_Simulations","235789051_Towards_Robust_Algorithms_for_Current_Deposition_and_Dynamic_Load-Balancing_in_a_GPU_Particle_In_Cell_Code","234913018_Linear_and_nonlinear